Layer 4: Application Layer
Combines OSI 7, 6, 5
HTTP, FTP, DNS, SMTP
SSL/TLS, Session Management

Layer 3: Transport Layer
Maps to OSI Layer 4
TCP, UDP
Port-based communication

Layer 2: Internet Layer
Maps to OSI Layer 3
IP, ICMP, IGMP
Routing & logical addressing

Layer 1: Network Access/Link Layer
Combines OSI 2 & 1
Ethernet, 802.11, ARP
Physical + Data Link

Key Differences:
✓ OSI: 7 strict layers, conceptual
✓ TCP/IP: 4 practical layers
✓ OSI: Protocol-independent framework
✓ TCP/IP: Built around Internet protocols
✓ TCP/IP merges adjacent layers for efficiency
